Imtiaz Suliman from Sentio Capital chose Vodacom as his stock pick of the day Although the company was under pressure recently, he thinks it is still very solid and defensive in nature. It has a good dividend yield of 5.5% and growth in terms of subscribers remains positive. Vodacom was also the third best performer on the top 40 index on Wednesday — an overall down day on the JSE. The company’s share price was up 2.3%. OR LISTEN TO THE FULL SHOW: